      "Apply the third truth: recognize that the suffering that has a cause can have an end. This is not wishful thinking — it is logical. If this suffering arises from craving, the ending of that craving would be its cessation. The cessation is possible.",
      "Apply the fourth truth: which element of the eightfold path is relevant right now? Is this a moment for right speech? Right effort? Right mindfulness? The path is not theoretical — it has a specific application to this moment.",
      "Reflect at day's end: where did you apply this framework today? Where did you miss it and simply react? This reflection is itself part of bhāvetabba — the development of the path.",
