      "When you reach the end of your path, pause. Stand for two or three breaths before turning. The pause is part of the practice — not dead time. Then turn deliberately and resume.",
      "When the mind wanders — into planning, commentary, memory — note 'wandering' or 'thinking' and return attention to the sensation of the foot. The return is the practice, just as in sitting.",
