      "Use the fifth reflection — kamma — as a daily question: what kamma am I making today? In speech, in action, in intention? This reflection has immediate practical application.",
      "When difficulty arises — illness, loss, ageing in a loved one — return to the relevant reflection not as consolation, but as clear seeing: 'This is the nature of conditioned existence. This was never absent. I simply did not see it clearly before.'",
